ining of selected applicants in their chosen field / project before giving financial assistance. Several castes of Muslim minority community also comes under EBC category. In Bihar state, around 130 castes are listed under the state govt\u2019s EBC category. Out of these, around 36 castes including Ansari, Julaha, Momin, Dhunia, Churihaar, Bakkho, Rangrej, Madar etc comes from Muslim community."}, "004-section": {"000-title": "Bihar CM EBC Entrepreneurship Scheme 2020 Benefits", "001-normal": "CM EBC Entrepreneurship Scheme will come into force from the current financial year after getting approval from the Bihar state cabinet. The new scheme will bring unprecedented socio-economic change among the members of EBCs because majority of castes under this category are either artisans or having traditional entrepreneurship. The assistance of Rs 10 lakh will endure their economic upliftment.", "002-normal": "Industries department has already prepared a proposal and it would be sent to cabinet secetariat department for putting up in the next cabinet meeting. Besides the state govt. of Bihar has also provided reservation to the members of EBCs in the three-tier Panchayati Raj Institutions to ensure socio-political upliftment of backward classes.", "003-normal": "Source / Reference Link: https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/patna/bihar-nitish-announces-financial-assistance-of-rs-10-lakh-to-extremely-backward-classes-youths/articleshow/73592749.cms"}}